@ computer science

{ History #computer-science-history

  Some hsitory snippets

  1623: Wilhelm Schickard designed and constructed the first working mechanical calculator.

  1673: Gottfried Leibniz deomstrated a digital mechanical calculater: the *Stepped Reckoner*.
  -
  Leibniz was also the first(?) person to document the binary number system.

  1820: Thomas de Colmar lauchned the mechanical calculator industry by releasing the simplified *arithmometer*.

  1822: Charles Babbage started the design of the first automatic mechanical calculator, the *difference engine* out of
  which developed the first programmable mechanical calculator, the *analyticl engine*.

  Adoption of the punched card system from the *Jaquard loom*.

  1843: Ada Lovelace wrote an algorithm to compute the Bernoulli numbers.

  1885: Herman Hollerith invented the tabulator which used punch cards to process statistical information.
  -
  His company would eventually become → Companies-Products/IBM

  1940's: In the era of the *Atanasoff-Berry computer* and the *ENIAC*, the term *computer* began to refer to these machines.

}
